# ============================================================
# Auth — Autenticación y verificación de token
# ============================================================

### 1. Obtener token CSRF (paso previo al login)
GET {{base}}/api/csrf-token

###

### 2. Login correcto — devuelve JWT
# Copiar el valor de "token" en la variable {{token}} del entorno
POST {{base}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json
X-CSRF-Token: {{csrf}}

{
  "email": "admin@empresa.com",
  "password": "contraseña_admin"
}

###

### 3. Login con credenciales incorrectas → 401
POST {{base}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json
X-CSRF-Token: {{csrf}}

{
  "email": "admin@empresa.com",
  "password": "password_mal"
}

###

### 4. Login sin cuerpo JSON → 400
POST {{base}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: text/plain
X-CSRF-Token: {{csrf}}

no-json

###

### 5. Login sin CSRF → 403
POST {{base}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@empresa.com",
  "password": "contraseña_admin"
}

###

### 6. Validar token JWT (endpoint interno Nginx)
GET {{base}}/api/auth/validacion
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 7. Validar con token inválido → 401
GET {{base}}/api/auth/validacion
Authorization: Bearer token.invalido.aqui

###

### 8. Healthcheck
GET {{base}}/api/health
